      • requestContextInitializer

        public ServletContextInitializer requestContextInitializer()
        Create a ServletContextInitializer bean used by Spring to add information to the servlet context. This is used in place of the <listener>...</listener> elements of web.xml. Note: This bean must be created as early as possible, hence the Order(0) annotation. The RequestContextListener instance adds request information to the current thread, allowing for session- and request-scoped beans to be created, which is necessary for OAuth2 to function properly.
        Returns:
        a ServletContextInitializer used to add the RequestContextListener

      • restTemplate

        public com.digitalglobe.platform2020.identity.authentication.SecuredRestTemplate restTemplate()
        Create a RestTemplate bean with information about the OAuth2 client, OAuth2 server, and custom interceptors to ensure that the current OAuth2 access token is persisted to any calls made by this application
        Returns:
        the SecuredRestTemplate object used to make point-to-point calls
